[[Image:AmtrakLogo.png|frame|Amtrak's logo from 1971 to 2000, the "inverted arrow," dubbed by critics as the "pointless arrow." On July&nbsp;6,&nbsp;2000 Amtrak unveiled "...a new logo whose shape and suggestion of movement convey the comfort and uniqueness of the rail experience."<ref name="pr-newlogo">{{cite press release | title = Amtrak Introduces Service Guarantee and New Corporate Brand Identity At Event At Los Angeles Union Station | publisher = Amtrak | date = 2000-07-06 | url = http://www.trainweb.com/news/2000g06a.html | accessdate = 2008-06-16 }}</ref>]]
