|-
| style="background:Lemonchiffon; text-align:center;"|'''Mode''' || style="background:Lemonchiffon; text-align:center;"|'''Revenue per passenger mile<ref>Except where noted, figures are from 2007. {{cite web | title=Table 3-16: Average Passenger Revenue per Passenger-Mile | url=http://www.bts.gov/publications/national_transportation_statistics/html/table_03_16.html | accessdate=2006-11-17 | work=Bureau of Transportation Statistics}}</ref>''' || style="background:Lemonchiffon; text-align:center;"|'''Energy consumption per passenger mile<ref name="bts-energy"/>''' || style="background:Lemonchiffon; text-align:center;"|'''Deaths per 100 million passenger miles'''<ref>Figures are from 2000. {{cite web | url=http://www.nsc.org/lrs/statfaq.aspx#Question10 | publisher=National Safety Council | title=Injury Facts | year=2002 | accessdate=2008-09-13 }}</ref>{{Dead link|date=February 2010}} || style="background:Lemonchiffon;"|'''Reliability<ref name="bts-ontime">Figures from 2007. {{cite web | title=Table 1-67: Amtrak On-Time Performance Trends and Hours of Delay by Cause | work=Bureau of Transportation Statistics | accessdate=2006-11-17 | url=http://www.bts.gov/publications/national_transportation_statistics/html/table_01_67.html}}; {{cite web | title=Table 1-60: Flight Operations Arriving On Time by the Largest U.S. Air Carriers | work=Bureau of Transportation Statistics | accessdate=2006-11-17 | url=http://www.bts.gov/publications/national_transportation_statistics/html/table_01_60.html}}</ref>'''
